{"questionId":"22204422","questionHtml":"<p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>n</mi><mi>th</mi></msup></math> derivative of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> is denoted by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>n</mi></mfenced></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Prove by induction that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>n</mi></mfenced></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mo>!</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>1</mn></msup><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;therefore true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>assume (that the result is) true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for statements such as “let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>” or “assume that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> is true”. The assumption of truth must be clear.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>k</mi></mfenced></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to differentiate the right-hand side with respect to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>:</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mo>d</mo><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>k</mi></mfenced></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to multiply top and bottom by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>k</mi></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence if the result is true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> then it is true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and as it is true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> it is true for all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> To obtain the final <em><strong>R1</strong></em>, at least five of the previous marks must have been awarded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[8 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22204422","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.12a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Let fx=1-ax-12, where ax<1, a≠0. The nth derivative of fx is denoted by fnx, n∈ℤ+. Prove by induction that fnx=an2n-1!1-ax-2n+1222n-1n-1!, n∈ℤ+.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 8]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}